ISKCON Bhakti Center for Education and Culture (ISKCON BCEC) 
ISKCON is a non-profit organization that works for social welfare. ISKCON has only one aim and that is spreading the values and teachings of our Vedas. ISKCON BCEC is a beautiful place for gaining such values and for making your life even more fruitful and meaningful. It is an unique Vedic and cultural Education Center. This center is determinedly trying to build up the spiritual and ethical fabric of society with the help of different cultural and spiritual educational programs.

Founder Acharya: Srila Prabhupada
His Divine Grace Srila Prabhupada is the founder acharya of ISKCON. On 17th September 1965, A.C. Bhaktivedanta Swami Srila Prabhupada entered the port of the New York City. His visit aimed to introduce a very old religion, which originated in India.

title: Desires! Srila Prabhupada giving insight on What is we should Desire and what we should not! #desire
Humility of Srila Prabhupada! When he refused to skip the line and go in Front! Teaching by Example!
description:
The profound humility of Srila Prabhupada! Despite being the Founder-Acharya of ISKCON and a world-renowned spiritual leader, he refused to skip the line and insisted on waiting like everyone else. A timeless lesson in humility, dignity, and leading by example. True leadership is shown through actions, not positions.

#SrilaPrabhupada #Humility #LeadByExample #ISKCON #SpiritualLeader #LifeLessons #TeachByExample #Respect #VaishnavaCulture #HumbleHeart #Bhakti #SpiritualWisdom #ISKCONLife #SpiritualIndia

ISKCON Bhakti Center for Education and Culture (ISKCON BCEC) 
ISKCON is a non-profit organization that works for social welfare. ISKCON has only one aim and that is spreading the values and teachings of our Vedas. ISKCON BCEC is a beautiful place for gaining such values and for making your life even more fruitful and meaningful. It is an unique Vedic and cultural Education Center. This center is determinedly trying to build up the spiritual and ethical fabric of society with the help of different cultural and spiritual educational programs.

Founder Acharya: Srila Prabhupada
His Divine Grace Srila Prabhupada is the founder acharya of ISKCON. On 17th September 1965, A.C. Bhaktivedanta Swami Srila Prabhupada entered the port of the New York City. His visit aimed to introduce a very old religion, which originated in India.

description:
On the auspicious day of the Bhagwat Katha, Shri Vittal Patil performed the sacred Tula Daan ceremony in memory of his beloved son, the Late Siddhant Vittal Patil. This profound gratitude and devotion is a timeless tradition that brings peace to departed souls while invoking divine blessings for the family.  

What is Tula Daan?
Tula Daan is a unique ritual where offerings, equal in weight to an individual, are donated with love and selflessness. It is believed to cleanse past karma, bring spiritual fulfillment, and connect families with divine grace.  

‚ú®Make Your Special Moments Divine with Tula Daan‚ú®  
You, too, can perform Tula Daan on occasions like:  
- Birthdays
- Marriage Anniversaries
- Annaprashan Ceremony (First Grain Feeding) 
- In Loving Memory of Departed Souls
- Any Special Occasion to Express Gratitude

üí´ Transform your cherished day into a divine offering and experience the joy of giving while blessing your loved ones.

ISKCON Bhakti Center for Education and Culture (ISKCON BCEC) 
ISKCON is a non-profit organization that works for social welfare. ISKCON has only one aim and that is spreading the values and teachings of our Vedas. ISKCON BCEC is a beautiful place for gaining such values and for making your life even more fruitful and meaningful. It is an unique Vedic and cultural Education Center. This center is determinedly trying to build up the spiritual and ethical fabric of society with the help of different cultural and spiritual educational programs.

Founder Acharya: Srila Prabhupada
His Divine Grace Srila Prabhupada is the founder acharya of ISKCON. On 17th September 1965, A.C. Bhaktivedanta Swami Srila Prabhupada entered the port of the New York City. His visit aimed to introduce a very old religion, which originated in India.

In this enlightening talk, HG Nandkishore Prabhu shares how chanting the Shuddha Naam can lead to the ultimate goal of Bhagvat Prapti (attaining the Supreme Lord). He emphasizes that to truly chant the Shuddha Naam, one must follow three essential principles:

Nitya: Chanting regularly with dedication.

Nirantar: Chanting constantly without a break.

Nirapradh: Chanting without offenses, with a pure heart.


By adhering to these principles, we can connect deeply with the Lord and progress on our spiritual journey towards attaining His divine grace.

title: Opening Hari Naam Sankirtan by HH Shri Krishna Chaitanya Swami Maharaj | World Holy Name Week #bliss
description:
Celebrate World Holy Name Week with the powerful and soul-lifting Hari Naam Sankirtan led by HH Shri Krishna Chaitanya Swami Maharaj, ISKCON‚Äôs Kirtan Minister. This grand kirtan marks the opening of a week dedicated to spreading the glories of the holy name around the world. Feel the divine vibrations and immerse yourself in the transcendental sound that cleanses the heart and uplifts the soul.

Hari Naam Sankirtan is the congregational chanting of the holy names of the Lord, a powerful method of spiritual connection and purification recommended by all scriptures. Experience the bliss of chanting together, as millions of devotees across the globe join in this celebration of love, unity, and devotion to the Supreme Lord.

Let's spread the message of peace, devotion, and spiritual awakening through the holy name! Share this video, chant with us, and experience the transformative power of Hari Naam!

ISKCON Bhakti Center for Education and Culture (ISKCON BCEC) 
ISKCON is a non-profit organization that works for social welfare. ISKCON has only one aim and that is spreading the values and teachings of our Vedas. ISKCON BCEC is a beautiful place for gaining such values and for making your life even more fruitful and meaningful. It is an unique Vedic and cultural Education Center. This center is determinedly trying to build up the spiritual and ethical fabric of society with the help of different cultural and spiritual educational programs.

Founder Acharya: Srila Prabhupada
His Divine Grace Srila Prabhupada is the founder acharya of ISKCON. On 17th September 1965, A.C. Bhaktivedanta Swami Srila Prabhupada entered the port of the New York City. His visit aimed to introduce a very old religion, which originated in India.

title: Miracle at Sea: Chanting the Hare Krishna Mahamantra Calms the Storm üåäüôè
description:
Miracle at Sea: The Power of Hare Krishna Mahamantra
During the Kanyakumari Yatra, devotees from ISKCON BCEC experienced a miraculous event while on a boat in the sea. As they sailed through the ocean, suddenly, huge waves began shaking the boat dangerously, filling everyone with fear. But in the midst of this chaos, the devotees did something incredible‚Äîthey began chanting the Hare Krishna Mahamantra loudly and with great devotion.

To everyone's amazement, not only did the chanting dispel their fear, but the turbulent sea also calmed down, restoring peace and safety to all aboard. This powerful experience demonstrates the transformative power of the Mahamantra and the protective grace of the Lord.

Watch this video to witness the miracle that unfolded at sea and be inspired by the unwavering faith and devotion of the ISKCON BCEC devotees.

ISKCON Bhakti Center for Education and Culture (ISKCON BCEC) 
ISKCON is a non-profit organization that works for social welfare. ISKCON has only one aim and that is spreading the values and teachings of our Vedas. ISKCON BCEC is a beautiful place for gaining such values and for making your life even more fruitful and meaningful. It is an unique Vedic and cultural Education Center. This center is determinedly trying to build up the spiritual and ethical fabric of society with the help of different cultural and spiritual educational programs.

Founder Acharya: Srila Prabhupada
His Divine Grace Srila Prabhupada is the founder acharya of ISKCON. On 17th September 1965, A.C. Bhaktivedanta Swami Srila Prabhupada entered the port of the New York City. His visit aimed to introduce a very old religion, which originated in India.

ISKCON BCEC is a beautiful place for gaining such values and for making your life even more fruitful and meaningful. It is an unique Vedic and cultural Education Center.
